land":"Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Goushill was born about 1135, in Lincolnshire, England, his father, Erneis Goushill, was 22 and his mother, Ailinore de Arncliffe, was 17. He married Adeline Ingrim before 1154, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died before 1205, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1135–Bef 1205":"umbes 1135–enne 1205","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1138–1185":"1138–1185","1154–1201":"1154–1201","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1115–1155":"1115–1155","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","before 1154":"enne 1154","Bef 1205":"enne 1205","1154":"1154","1120":"1120","1241":"1241","1185":"1185","Abt 1185":"umbes 1185","1205":"1205","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","Abt 1135":"umbes 1135","1201":"1201","1135":"1135","Abt 1155":"umbes 1155","1155":"1155","after 1185":"pärast 1185","about 1154":"umbes 1154","Sproatley, Yorkshire, England":"Sproatley, Yorkshire, England","Goxhill, Yorkshire, England":"Goxhill, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Goxhill, Lincolnshire, England":"Goxhill, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1135–Bef 1205":"noin 1135–ennen vuotta 1205","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1138–1185":"1138–1185","1154–1201":"1154–1201","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1115–1155":"1115–1155","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","before 1154":"ennen vuotta 1154","Bef 1205":"ennen vuotta 1205","1154":"1154","1120":"1120","1241":"1241","1185":"1185","Abt 1185":"noin 1185","1205":"1205","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","Abt 1135":"noin 1135","1201":"1201","1135":"1135","Abt 1155":"noin 1155","1155":"1155","after 1185":"1185 jälkeen","about 1154":"noin 1154","Sproatley, Yorkshire, England":"Sproatley, Yorkshire, England","Goxhill, Yorkshire, England":"Goxhill, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Goxhill, Lincolnshire, England":"Goxhill, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1135–Bef 1205":"environ 1135–avant 1205","1135–1205":"1135–1205","1138–1185":"1138–1185","1154–1201":"1154–1201","1185–1241":"1185–1241","1115–1155":"1115–1155","1120–Female":"1120–Décédée","before 1154":"avant 1154","Bef 1205":"avant 1205","1154":"1154","1120":"1120","1241":"1241"